# Blog UI Components

## Overview

The blog system uses a set of reusable UI components for displaying blog posts in various layouts. These components follow the existing design patterns from product cards and carousels.

## Components

### BlogCard (`BlogCard.tsx`)

Default/desktop blog post card with vertical layout.

**Features:**
- White background with thick pink border (`border-2 border-pink-100`)
- Featured image with aspect ratio `304:260`
- "اینفینیتی" watermark overlay on image
- Category and date metadata with visible icons (`text-neutral-400`)
- Title and excerpt with line clamping
- Hover effects with shadow and scale

**Props:**
```typescript
interface BlogCardProps {
  post: BlogPost;
  priority?: boolean;  // Image loading priority
  className?: string;
}
```

**Usage:**
```tsx
<BlogCard post={post} priority={index === 0} />
```

### BlogCardMobile (`BlogCardMobile.tsx`)

Compact horizontal blog card for mobile layouts.

**Features:**
- Horizontal layout with image on the right
- Fixed image size: 110x110px
- Same styling as BlogCard (thick border, visible icons, watermark)
- Condensed metadata and content

**Props:**
```typescript
interface BlogCardMobileProps {
  post: BlogPost;
  priority?: boolean;
  className?: string;
}
```

### BlogCarousel (`BlogCarousel.tsx`)

Responsive carousel for displaying blog posts with pagination.

**Features:**
- Desktop: 4 cards per page with pagination controls
- Mobile: 4 stacked cards with "مشاهده همه" button
- Category filtering support
- Dynamic title and button text
- Loading skeleton state

**Props:**
```typescript
interface BlogCarouselProps {
  posts?: BlogPost[];           // Pre-fetched posts
  category?: string;            // Category slug for filtering
  title: string;                // Section title
  viewAllHref?: string;         // Custom view all link
  isCategory?: boolean;         // Show "مشاهده دسته بندی" vs "مشاهده همه"
  className?: string;
}
```

**Usage Examples:**

```tsx
// With pre-fetched posts
<BlogCarousel
  posts={latestPosts}
  title="جدیدترین مقالات"
/>

// With category filtering (fetches posts automatically)
<BlogCarousel
  category="mod-o-poshak"
  title="مد و پوشاک"
  isCategory
/>
```

### BlogCategoryBanner (`BlogCategoryBanner.tsx`)

Featured banner for category promotion between carousel sections.

**Features:**
- Customizable background (gradient or image)
- Light/dark text color variants
- Three height sizes: sm, md, lg
- Centered content with title, subtitle, and CTA button

**Props:**
```typescript
interface BlogCategoryBannerProps {
  title: string;
  subtitle?: string;
  backgroundImage?: string;
  backgroundColor?: string;      // Tailwind gradient class
  href: string;
  linkText?: string;
  textColor?: "light" | "dark";
  height?: "sm" | "md" | "lg";
  className?: string;
}
```

**Usage:**
```tsx
<BlogCategoryBanner
  title="مد و پوشاک"
  subtitle="آخرین ترندها و نکات استایل"
  href="/blog?category=mod-o-poshak"
  backgroundColor="bg-gradient-to-br from-rose-400 to-pink-600"
  textColor="light"
  linkText="مشاهده دسته بندی"
  height="sm"
/>
```

## Blog Page Structure

The `/blog` page follows this layout:

1. **Hero Section** - Page title and description
2. **Latest Posts Carousel** - Most recent posts
3. **Category Sections** - Each category with its own carousel
4. **Banners** - Promotional banners between category sections
5. **Footer Banner** - "View all articles" CTA

## Styling Guidelines

### Colors
- Border: `border-pink-100` (hover: `border-pink-200`)
- Icons: `text-neutral-400`
- Text: `text-neutral-700` (title), `text-neutral-400` (meta)
- Watermark: `text-neutral-600` on `bg-white/80`

### Spacing
- Card padding: `p-3` (desktop), `p-2` (mobile)
- Card gap: `gap-4`
- Section spacing: `space-y-12`

### Border Radius
- Cards: `rounded-3xl` (outer), `rounded-[20px]` (image)
- Mobile cards: `rounded-2xl` (outer), `rounded-xl` (image)
- Banners: `rounded-[32px]`

## RTL Support

All components are designed for RTL layouts:
- Text alignment: `text-right`
- Flex direction: Default (respects `dir="rtl"`)
- Icons: Positioned on the right side of text

## Performance

- Images use `BlurImage` with `imageLoader` for optimization
- Priority loading for first visible card
- Skeleton loading states during data fetch
- Lazy loading for off-screen images

